The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (Landmark, Rs 1,495)If it?s one DVD you will buy in the season of giving, make it this one. The proceeds go to famine relief in Africa. Four discs try to capture the glorious get-together of the music fraternity in a series of concerts held in July 2005. U2 to Pink Floyd, Madonna to Mariah Carey, and a lot more.

 THE DISPLAY

 (Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 7 pm, till Dec 31)

 The work of the German lensman features glimpses of Asian megacities, titled Neontigers, and contemporary German landscape, called Heimat.

 THE SHOW

 (Academy of Fine Arts, December 25) The curtains come down on the annual festival hosted by Nandikar with a string of three plays. Dhaka Theatre?s Binodini at 10.30 am, Swapnasandhani?s Bhalo Rakshasher Galpo at 2.30 pm and Bappaditya at 6 pm.




